    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In ancient China, stone structures resembling watchtowers which marked the entrance to a building complex. Generally built in pairs, they stand on opposing sides of a road or walkway, and are typically found in front of citadels, palaces, mansions, ancestral temples, and mausoleums.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
